data.title: Office of Missouri Lieutenant Governor – Missouri Lieutenant Governor
data.text:
Mike Kehoe was sworn in as Missouri’s 48th Lieutenant Governor on June 18, 2018, after being appointed to the position by Governor Mike Parson. He was elected by Missourians to a full term on Nov. 3, 2020.

From very humble beginnings, through hard work, determination, and the influence of his mother and the help of his mentor, Kehoe went on to become a successful businessman, a husband, and a father, before running for office.

Thank you for contacting the Lieutenant Governor’s Office and requesting his attendance at your event. For a quick response, please fill out the form below. The required information is designated with an asterisk (*). You may also mail your request to:

Lieutenant Governor’s Office

State Capitol, Room 224

Jefferson City, MO 65101
